<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<Defs>

  <FactionColonies.FCEventDef>
    <defName>empireEvents_corruption_0</defName>
    <label>Corruption Scandal</label>
    <desc>Local officials in your settlements have been caught skimming taxes. Citizens are furious; trust in your administration is eroding quickly. How do you handle this?</desc>
    <category>EC_Economy</category>
    <timeTillTrigger>0</timeTillTrigger>
    <activateAtStart>true</activateAtStart>
    <cooldownTicks>600000</cooldownTicks>
    <isRandomEvent>true</isRandomEvent>
    <weight>15</weight>
    <minimumProsperity>50</minimumProsperity>
    <minSettlements>2</minSettlements>
    <minDaysSinceFounded>15</minDaysSinceFounded>
    <rangeSettlementsAffected>1~2</rangeSettlementsAffected>
    <incompatibleEvents>
      <li>empireEvents_corruption_1a</li>
      <li>empireEvents_corruption_1b</li>
      <li>empireEvents_corruption_1c</li>
      <li>empireEvents_corruption_1d</li>
      <li>empireEvents_corruption_1e</li>
    </incompatibleEvents>
    <options>
      <li>empireEvents_corruption_opt1</li>
      <li>empireEvents_corruption_opt2</li>
      <li>empireEvents_corruption_opt3</li>
      <li>empireEvents_corruption_opt4</li>
      <li>empireEvents_corruption_opt5</li>
    </options>
  </FactionColonies.FCEventDef>

  <FactionColonies.FCOptionDef>
    <defName>empireEvents_corruption_opt1</defName>
    <label>Hold a public trial. Justice must be seen to be done.</label>
    <parentEvent>empireEvents_corruption_0</parentEvent>
    <baseChanceOfSuccess>100</baseChanceOfSuccess>
    <successEvent>empireEvents_corruption_1a</successEvent>
  </FactionColonies.FCOptionDef>

  <FactionColonies.FCOptionDef>
    <defName>empireEvents_corruption_opt2</defName>
    <label>Replace them quietly. No need to make a spectacle.</label>
    <parentEvent>empireEvents_corruption_0</parentEvent>
    <baseChanceOfSuccess>100</baseChanceOfSuccess>
    <successEvent>empireEvents_corruption_1b</successEvent>
  </FactionColonies.FCOptionDef>

  <FactionColonies.FCOptionDef>
    <defName>empireEvents_corruption_opt3</defName>
    <label>Legitimize the skimming as an "administrative fee." It's not corruption if it's policy.</label>
    <parentEvent>empireEvents_corruption_0</parentEvent>
    <baseChanceOfSuccess>100</baseChanceOfSuccess>
    <successEvent>empireEvents_corruption_1c</successEvent>
  </FactionColonies.FCOptionDef>

  <FactionColonies.FCOptionDef>
    <defName>empireEvents_corruption_opt4</defName>
    <label>Execute the corrupt officials publicly.</label>
    <parentEvent>empireEvents_corruption_0</parentEvent>
    <baseChanceOfSuccess>100</baseChanceOfSuccess>
    <successEvent>empireEvents_corruption_1d</successEvent>
    <requiredPolicies>
      <li>authoritarian</li>
    </requiredPolicies>
  </FactionColonies.FCOptionDef>

  <FactionColonies.FCOptionDef>
    <defName>empireEvents_corruption_opt5</defName>
    <label>Establish an oversight committee.</label>
    <parentEvent>empireEvents_corruption_0</parentEvent>
    <baseChanceOfSuccess>100</baseChanceOfSuccess>
    <silverCost>200</silverCost>
    <successEvent>empireEvents_corruption_1e</successEvent>
    <requiredPolicies>
      <li>egalitarian</li>
    </requiredPolicies>
  </FactionColonies.FCOptionDef>

  <FactionColonies.FCEventDef>
    <defName>empireEvents_corruption_1a</defName>
    <label>Public Trial</label>
    <desc>The corrupt officials are tried before the people and removed from their posts. Citizens are heartened by the display of justice, though replacing the administrators — who were actually quite competent at their jobs — takes time.</desc>
    <category>EC_Economy</category>
    <timeTillTrigger>300000</timeTillTrigger>
    <timeTillTriggerMax>450000</timeTillTriggerMax>
    <rangeSettlementsAffected>1~2</rangeSettlementsAffected>
    <incompatibleEvents>
      <li>empireEvents_corruption_0</li>
    </incompatibleEvents>
    <statModifiers>
      <li>
        <stat>loyaltyGainedBase</stat>
        <value>2</value>
      </li>
      <li>
        <stat>workerBaseMax</stat>
        <value>-1</value>
      </li>
    </statModifiers>
  </FactionColonies.FCEventDef>

  <FactionColonies.FCEventDef>
    <defName>empireEvents_corruption_1b</defName>
    <label>Officials Replaced</label>
    <desc>The corrupt officials are quietly reassigned. Business returns to normal quickly, but without public accountability, there's nothing stopping the next batch from doing the same thing.</desc>
    <category>EC_Economy</category>
    <timeTillTrigger>60000</timeTillTrigger>
    <rangeSettlementsAffected>1~2</rangeSettlementsAffected>
    <incompatibleEvents>
      <li>empireEvents_corruption_0</li>
    </incompatibleEvents>
    <followingEvent>empireEvents_corruption_recur</followingEvent>
    <followingEvent2>Null</followingEvent2>
    <splitEventFollows>true</splitEventFollows>
    <splitEventChance>40</splitEventChance>
  </FactionColonies.FCEventDef>

  <FactionColonies.FCEventDef>
    <defName>empireEvents_corruption_recur</defName>
    <label>Corruption Returns</label>
    <desc>It turns out that refusing to hold criminals accountable can come with drawbacks. New officials have picked up where the old ones left off, and their corruption is even more brazen. Without a public example, corruption has become an expected perk of office. Tax revenues suffer again.</desc>
    <category>EC_Economy</category>
    <timeTillTrigger>300000</timeTillTrigger>
    <timeTillTriggerMax>900000</timeTillTriggerMax>
    <rangeSettlementsAffected>1~2</rangeSettlementsAffected>
    <statModifiers>
      <li>
        <stat>taxBasePercentage</stat>
        <value>-10</value>
      </li>
      <li>
        <stat>unrestGainedBase</stat>
        <value>1</value>
      </li>
    </statModifiers>
  </FactionColonies.FCEventDef>

  <FactionColonies.FCEventDef>
    <defName>empireEvents_corruption_1c</defName>
    <label>Administrative Fees</label>
    <desc>The "administrative fee" is now official policy. Tax revenues actually improve slightly as the fees are now collected openly, but citizens see right through the relabeling. Resentment boils over as the brazen corruption is enshrined in law.</desc>
    <category>EC_Economy</category>
    <timeTillTrigger>600000</timeTillTrigger>
    <rangeSettlementsAffected>1~2</rangeSettlementsAffected>
    <incompatibleEvents>
      <li>empireEvents_corruption_0</li>
    </incompatibleEvents>
    <statModifiers>
      <li>
        <stat>unrestGainedBase</stat>
        <value>2</value>
      </li>
      <li>
        <stat>taxBasePercentage</stat>
        <value>5</value>
      </li>
    </statModifiers>
  </FactionColonies.FCEventDef>

  <FactionColonies.FCEventDef>
    <defName>empireEvents_corruption_1d</defName>
    <label>Public Executions</label>
    <desc>The corrupt officials are executed before a stunned crowd. The message is unmistakable: the empire does not tolerate betrayal. Citizens are both terrified and oddly reassured — at least their leaders take corruption seriously.</desc>
    <category>EC_Economy</category>
    <timeTillTrigger>120000</timeTillTrigger>
    <timeTillTriggerMax>240000</timeTillTriggerMax>
    <rangeSettlementsAffected>1~2</rangeSettlementsAffected>
    <incompatibleEvents>
      <li>empireEvents_corruption_0</li>
    </incompatibleEvents>
    <statModifiers>
      <li>
        <stat>unrestGainedBase</stat>
        <value>1</value>
      </li>
      <li>
        <stat>loyaltyGainedBase</stat>
        <value>1</value>
      </li>
    </statModifiers>
  </FactionColonies.FCEventDef>

  <FactionColonies.FCEventDef>
    <defName>empireEvents_corruption_1e</defName>
    <label>Oversight Committee</label>
    <desc>A citizen oversight committee is established to monitor government spending. The corrupt officials are removed through due process, and the new transparency lifts morale. The system works — and citizens have a voice in keeping it honest.</desc>
    <category>EC_Economy</category>
    <timeTillTrigger>300000</timeTillTrigger>
    <rangeSettlementsAffected>1~2</rangeSettlementsAffected>
    <incompatibleEvents>
      <li>empireEvents_corruption_0</li>
    </incompatibleEvents>
    <statModifiers>
      <li>
        <stat>happinessGainedBase</stat>
        <value>0.5</value>
      </li>
    </statModifiers>
  </FactionColonies.FCEventDef>

</Defs>
